{
  "texts": [
    "This may apply, for example, to some of the tasks performed by priests, judges, or lawmakers.",
    "We lay out an economic model in which atomistic tasks are gross complements that are combined to produce nal goods.",
    "In the spirit of Zeira (1998) and Acemoglu and Restrepo (2018, 2022), all tasks can be performed by labor, and automated tasks can be performed by either labor or capital.",
    "However, unlike in the described works, our main focus is on the edge cases that arise as we come close to full automation.",
    "Our analysis begins by examining the equilibrium under xed supplies of capital and labor."
  ]
}